.TH TTSC 1 "March 2025" "Dawnstar ReadAloud 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ttsc \- TTS daemon client for low-latency speech synthesis
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ttsc
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ttsc
is a command-line client for the TTS daemon (ttsd). It provides instant
speech synthesis with no startup delay by communicating with a background
daemon process.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B speak \fITEXT\fR
Speak the provided text immediately
.TP
.B speak\-selection
Speak the current clipboard/primary selection
.TP
.B stop
Stop current playback and clear queue
.TP
.B pause
Pause current playback
.TP
.B resume
Resume paused playback
.TP
.B status
Show daemon status (state, queue size, current job)
.TP
.B voices
List available voices/languages
.TP
.B shutdown
Shutdown the daemon
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-socket\fR=\fIPATH\fR
Path to daemon socket (default: $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tts-daemon.sock)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Speak text:
ttsc speak "Hello world"
.TP
Speak clipboard content:
ttsc speak-selection
.TP
Check daemon status:
ttsc status
.TP
Stop playback:
ttsc stop
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tts-daemon.sock
Unix socket for daemon communication
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tts (1),
.BR ttsd (1)
